{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781717026468,"sessionID":"ses_12966050effeaSiftYGUJbFTz1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_2a2de9c70ee94cbf85a2124d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md","oldString":"## Review Dimensions\n\n- [ ] D1: Correctness — Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2: Security — Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3: Traceability — Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4: Maintainability — Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes","newString":"## Completed Dimensions\n\n- [x] D1: Correctness — PASS. 3 P2 advisories (lag drift, missing TTL warning, cache-hit cancel gap). No logic errors, no broken invariants. [iteration 1]\n\n## Review Dimensions\n\n- [ ] D2: Security — Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3: Traceability — Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4: Maintainability — Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md\n@@ -3,11 +3,14 @@\n ## Topic\n \n Review of cooperative heavy phases keep the daemon responsive (spec folder 021-cooperative-heavy-phases). The reindex scan now measures event-loop lag and per-phase wall-clock; the trigger-embedding-backfill transaction is chunked and cancellable; and each un-yielded tail phase refreshes the maintenance marker on entry.\n \n+## Completed Dimensions\n+\n+- [x] D1: Correctness — PASS. 3 P2 advisories (lag drift, missing TTL warning, cache-hit cancel gap). No logic errors, no broken invariants. [iteration 1]\n+\n ## Review Dimensions\n \n-- [ ] D1: Correctness — Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n - [ ] D2: Security — Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n - [ ] D3: Traceability — Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n - [ ] D4: Maintainability — Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md\n@@ -3,11 +3,14 @@\n ## Topic\n \n Review of cooperative heavy phases keep the daemon responsive (spec folder 021-cooperative-heavy-phases). The reindex scan now measures event-loop lag and per-phase wall-clock; the trigger-embedding-backfill transaction is chunked and cancellable; and each un-yielded tail phase refreshes the maintenance marker on entry.\n \n+## Completed Dimensions\n+\n+- [x] D1: Correctness — PASS. 3 P2 advisories (lag drift, missing TTL warning, cache-hit cancel gap). No logic errors, no broken invariants. [iteration 1]\n+\n ## Review Dimensions\n \n-- [ ] D1: Correctness — Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n - [ ] D2: Security — Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n - [ ] D3: Traceability — Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n - [ ] D4: Maintainability — Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes\n \n","additions":4,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781717026465,"end":1781717026467}},"id":"prt_ed69c4699001OvOJSelSJ7ovxO","sessionID":"ses_12966050effeaSiftYGUJbFTz1","messageID":"msg_ed69c15c9001E5ch6Fyjp37ECQ"}}
