{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781717063858,"sessionID":"ses_12966050effeaSiftYGUJbFTz1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_1fcd06b2770c4e44a11b2227","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Review Report: cooperative heavy phases keep the daemon responsive\n\n> Auto-generated by deep-review synthesis.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Verdict** | **PASS** |\n| **hasAdvisories** | true |\n| **Scope** | 3 implementation files + 4 spec/plan files in 021-cooperative-heavy-phases |\n| **Iterations** | 1 |\n| **Stop Reason** | maxIterations (1/1 used) |\n| **Convergence** | maxIterations reached; no P0/P1 findings present |\n\n**Active Findings:** P0: 0 | P1: 0 | P2: 3\n\nNo P0 or P1 findings were discovered. Three P2 advisory findings are recorded. The implementation correctly delivers the three load-bearing changes (lag sampler, chunked trigger-backfill, per-tail-phase marker refresh) and the spec's normative claims all have concrete file:line verification.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Planning Trigger\n\nThe verdict is **PASS** with advisories. No remediation planning is required. The three P2 findings are suggestions for minor observability and correctness hardening improvements. Follow-up action: `/create:changelog` for the 021 phase.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Active Finding Registry\n\n| ID | Severity | Dimension | Title | File:Line | First Seen | Status |\n|----|----------|-----------|-------|-----------|------------|--------|\n| F001 | P2 | Correctness | Lag sampler expectedAt drift accumulation | `memory-index.ts:512` | 1 | active |\n| F002 | P2 | Correctness | timedPhase missing TTL-exceed warning | `memory-index.ts:1226` | 1 | active |\n| F003 | P2 | Correctness | Cache-hit yield missing isCancelled at yield point | `trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:282` | 1 | active |\n\n### Finding Details\n\n**F001** — Lag sampler `expectedAt` resets to `sampledAt + LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS` on each tick. A late tick (GC pause) inflates the next lag measurement by the same amount. Self-correcting after one tick. Overstatement is conservative (reports worse than actual). [SOURCE: memory-index.ts:512-516]\n\n**F002** — `timedPhase` logs `phase=<label> ms=<elapsed>` and fires `ctx.onPhase` (marker refresh), but does not annotate when elapsed exceeds the 180s marker TTL. A deploy-time operator must manually correlate. Raw data is present for diagnosis. [SOURCE: memory-index.ts:1226-1237]\n\n**F003** — Cache-hit fast path yields every 50 iterations but checks `isCancelled` only at loop top (line 275), not at the yield point. Cancellation during a burst of 50 cache hits defers to the next boundary (up to 49 extra iterations). Bounded and non-destructive. [SOURCE: trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:274-284]\n\n---\n\n## 4. Remediation Workstreams\n\nNo remediation required (PASS verdict). The three P2 findings form a single optional improvement workstream:\n\n**WS-1: Observability and cancellation hardening (P2, optional)**\n- F001: Anchor lag sampler to absolute cadence instead of sampledAt\n- F002: Add structured warning when timedPhase exceeds 180s TTL\n- F003: Add isCancelled check at cache-hit yield point\n\n---\n\n## 5. Spec Seed\n\nNo spec changes required. All normative claims (REQ-001 through REQ-004) are verified against the implementation. The spec accurately describes the delivered behavior.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Plan Seed\n\nNo plan changes required. The implementation matches the plan's architecture (3 cooperating changes: lag sampler + timedPhase, chunked trigger-backfill, isCancelled threading). All plan quality gates pass.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Traceability Status\n\n### Core Protocols (hard-gated)\n\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|\n| spec_code | **pass** | hard | All 6 normative claims verified: REQ-001 (lag sampler gated on ctx.onPhase), REQ-002 (chunk transactions with between-chunk yields), REQ-003 (timedPhase fires onPhase per tail phase), REQ-004 (launcher confirmed correct), foreground path byte-identical (instrument flag), no yield inside transaction |\n| checklist_evidence | **skipped** | hard | No checklist.md in Level 1 spec folder |\n\n### Overlay Protocols (advisory)\n\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|\n| feature_catalog_code | **pass** | advisory | Lag sampler (memory-index.ts:501-526), chunked backfill (trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:169-259), per-phase refresh (memory-index.ts:1226-1261) all verified in code |\n\nNo unresolved protocol gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Deferred Items\n\n| ID | Type | Description | Rationale |\n|----|------|-------------|-----------|\n| F001 | P2 advisory | Lag drift accumulation | Conservative overstatement; self-correcting |\n| F002 | P2 advisory | Missing TTL-exceed annotation | Raw data present; structured warning is convenience |\n| F003 | P2 advisory | Cache-hit cancel gap | Bounded (49 iterations max), non-destructive |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Audit Appendix\n\n### Coverage Matrix\n\n| File | Reviewed | Findings | Notes |\n|------|----------|----------|-------|\n| `handlers/memory-index.ts` | ✅ | F001, F002 | Lag sampler, timedPhase, isCancelled threading |\n| `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` | ✅ | F003 | Chunk loop, cache-hit yield, isCancelled |\n| `tests/trigger-embedding-backfill.vitest.ts` | ✅ | — | 3 cancel/yield cases verified correct |\n| `spec.md` | ✅ | — | Normative claims all verified |\n| `plan.md` | ✅ | — | Architecture matches implementation |\n| `implementation-summary.md` | ✅ | — | Verification table cross-checked |\n\n### Dimension Breakdown\n\n| Dimension | Covered | Iterations | Findings |\n|-----------|---------|------------|----------|\n| Correctness | ✅ | 1 | 3 P2 |\n| Security | ❌ | 0 | 0 |\n| Traceability | ❌ | 0 | 0 |\n| Maintainability | ❌ | 0 | 0 |\n\nNote: With maxIterations=1, only one dimension received coverage. The PASS verdict is based on the correctness dimension showing no P0/P1 findings and the core spec_code traceability protocol passing. Security, traceability, and maintainability dimensions were not reviewed due to the iteration cap.\n\n### Convergence Evidence\n\n- Stop reason: maxIterations (1/1 iterations used)\n- New findings ratio: 0.0 (all P2 findings, no P0/P1)\n- Composite stop score: 0.0\n- All P2 findings survived adversarial self-check (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee pattern applied to each)\n\n### Claim Adjudication\n\nAll 3 findings (F001, F002, F003) carry typed adjudication packets in iteration-001.md. All packets pass validation: required fields present, evidenceRefs contain file:line citations, finalSeverity matches registered severity, confidence in [0,1], downgradeTrigger specified.\n\n### Verdict Determination\n\n| Gate | Result |\n|------|--------|\n| P0 Resolution | ✅ No P0 findings |\n| Evidence Density | ✅ All findings cite file:line |\n| Scope Fidelity | ✅ All reviewed files in declared scope |\n| Claim Adjudication | ✅ All P0/P1 packets valid (N/A: no P0/P1) |\n\n**Final Verdict: PASS** — No active P0 or P1 findings. Three P2 advisories recorded with `hasAdvisories: true`.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/review-report.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/review-report.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p021-mimo-2/review-report.md","time":{"start":1781717063851,"end":1781717063856}},"id":"prt_ed69cd8a5001EsHZEjAlL7gdXr","sessionID":"ses_12966050effeaSiftYGUJbFTz1","messageID":"msg_ed69c6f37001uEtBF8ssCbTc14"}}
